data.title: Category:Coats of arms of Grand Duchy of Lithuania
data.text:
Coat of arms of Grand Duchy of Lithuania has been a permanent heraldic element of Grand Duchy of Lithuania over the centuries

and has been derived from the coat of arms of the Gediminid Dynasty and its branches, whose descendants still live in Poland today.

Shortly after it became the emblem of Wladislaus II of Poland, and in the future it would be an inseparable part of the coat of arms of the Polish-Lithuanian Commonwealth as well as its rulers.

Nowadays, the coat of arms of Grand Duchy of Lithuania is the national coat of arms of Lithuania, coat of arms of many Polish cities and Podlaskie Voivodeship. The rights to the national heritage of the coat of arms of the Grand Duchy of Lithuania are claimed by present-day Lithuania, Poland and Belarus.

The category includes coats of arms with the emblem of the state of the Grand Duchy of Lithuania and its derivatives, as well as other closely related elements.
